For more details, see [Authorization for APIs to read Office 365 usage reports](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/reportroot-authorization?view=graph-rest-1.0).

For more details, see [Authorization for APIs to read Office 365 usage reports](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/reportroot-authorization?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Added the **groupId** property to the [office365GroupsActivityDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/office365GroupsActivityDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added the **ownerPrincipalName** property to the [oneDriveUsageAccountDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/oneDriveUsageAccountDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added the **ownerPrincipalName** property to the [sharePointSiteUsageDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/sharePointSiteUsageDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added the **office365Active** and **office365Inactive** properties to the [office365ServicesUserCounts](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/office365ServicesUserCounts?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added **deletedItemCount** property to the [mailboxUsageDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/mailboxUsageDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added **deletedItemSizeInBytes** property to the [mailboxUsageDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/mailboxUsageDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added **groupId** property to the [office365GroupsActivityDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/office365GroupsActivityDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added new reports for retrieving user registration and usage information:,
  • [reportroot-getcredentialusagesummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-getcredentialusagesummary?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset.
  • [reportroot-getcredentialuserregistrationcount](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-getcredentialuserregistrationcount?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports the number of registrations for self-service password reset and multi-factor authentication.
  • [reportroot-list-credentialuserregistrationdetails](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-list-credentialuserregistrationdetails?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset and multi-factor authentication.
  • [reportroot-list-usercredentialusagedetails](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/reportroot-list-usercredentialusagedetails?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset for a user.
Added **ownerPrincipalName** property to the [oneDriveUsageAccountDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/oneDriveUsageAccountDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added **ownerPrincipalName** property to the [sharePointSiteUsageDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/sharePointSiteUsageDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added the **office365Active** and **office365Inactive** properties to the [office365ServicesUserCounts](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/office365ServicesUserCounts?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Insights API is available in v1.0. This includes the [officeGraphInsights](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/officegraphinsights?view=graph-rest-1.0), [trending](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-trending?view=graph-rest-1.0), [usedInsight](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-used?view=graph-rest-1.0), and [sharedInsight](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-shared?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources, and related types and methods. See [Why integrate with document-based insights?](social-intel-concept-overview.md#why-integrate-with-document-based-insights) for more information.
Added the [profile API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/profile?view=graph-rest-beta) and associated methods.

Introduced the new workplace intelligence [analytics API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/useranalytics?view=graph-rest-beta) that enables you to get analytics about how users spend their time on various activities during and outside of working hours, including calls, chats (instant messages), emails, focus work, and meetings.

Introduced the new workplace intelligence [settings API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/settings?view=graph-rest-beta) that represents the current required settings for a user to use the [analytics API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/useranalytics?view=graph-rest-beta).

Introduced the new [activityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type and the following new resource types that are derived from it: [callActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/callactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), [chatActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/chatactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta),[emailActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/emailactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), [focusActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/focusactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), and [meetingActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/meetingactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta).

ChangeList.Description: Added delegated permission [EntitlementManagement.Read.All](permissions-reference.md#entitlement-management-permissions).
Added support for [delta queries for application](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/application-delta?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added new entity type: [servicePrincipal](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/serviceprincipal?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added new entity type: [appRoleAssignment](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/approleassignment?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added app-only and delegated permissions [AppRoleAssignment.ReadWrite.All](permissions-reference.md#application-resource-permissions).
Added the **externalUserState** and **externalUserStateChangeDateTime** properties to the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.
Added support for [subscription](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/subscription) to the **user** resource in [Microsoft Cloud China operated by 21Vianet](deployments.md).

Added [unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple?view=graph-rest-beta), [rbacApplicationMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/rbacapplicationmultiple?view=graph-rest-beta), and [appScope](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/appscope?view=graph-rest-beta) and the following actions:
  • [List unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple-list?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [Get unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple-get?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [Create unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple-post?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [Update unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple-update?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [Delete unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple-delete?view=graph-rest-beta)
    • .
Added support for [delta queries for administrativeUnits](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/administrativeunit-delta?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added support for [delta queries for oAuth2PermissionGrant](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/oauth2permissiongrant-delta?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added the [authenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/authenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta), [passwordAuthenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/passwordauthenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta), and [phoneAuthenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/phoneauthenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta) resources and associated methods.
Added the **createdByAppId** property to the [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Typed policy resources are grouped under the [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-1.0) URL segment. This update adds five typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) and
  • [tokenIssuancePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

Added the [claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

Added the [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

Added the [tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.

Added the [tokenIssuancePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the characteristics of SAML tokens issued by Azure AD. This allows you to set the signing algorithm, signing options, or SAML token version to be used to issue the SAML token.

Added the PrivilegedAccess.Read.AzureResources application permission for [Privileged Identity Management - Azure resources](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/privilegedidentitymanagement-resources?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added the [Auditlogs.Read.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#user-permissions) permission for listing the sign-in activity of a user.

Added the [identitySecurityDefaultsEnforcementPolicy API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/identitysecuritydefaultsenforcementpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta), which represents Azure Active Directory security defaults policy.
Added support for the **$top** and **$skiptoken** filters to support pagination on the [List provisioningObjectSummary](/api-reference/beta/api/provisioningobjectsummary-list) method.
Added the **authenticationRequirement** property and the **riskEventTypes_v2** property to the [signin](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/signin?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Added support for [delta queries for orgContact](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/orgcontact-delta?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added new user permission [User.ManageIdentities.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#user-permissions).
Updated the conditional access APIs to use the /identity/ segment; for example, /beta/identity/conditionalAccess/policies.
Added the **devices** property to the [conditionalaccessconditionset](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/conditionalaccessconditionset?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added the [group: assignLicense API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/group-assignlicense?view=graph-rest-1.0), which can be used to assign license to a [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Updated the existing policies collection with a [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-beta) URL segment. Typed policy resources are now grouped under the policies segment as described in [this blog post](https://developer.microsoft.com/identity/blogs/breaking-changes-policy-api-microsoft-graph-beta/). This update adds four typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) and
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

Added the [claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

Added the [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

Added the [tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.

Added the [tokenIssuancePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the characteristics of SAML tokens issued by Azure AD. This allows you to set the signing algorithm, signing options, or SAML token version to be used to issue the SAML token.
Added the [error](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/synchronization-synchronizationError?view=graph-rest-beta) property to the **quarantineStatus** resource type.

Updated the [accessPackageAssignmentPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/accesspackageassignmentpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) with additional properties for requestor, approval and review settings.

Added the **latestSupportedTlsVersion** property to the [subscription](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/subscription?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity. Specifies the latest TLS version that the notification endpoint supports. Allows subscribers to use a deprecated version of TLS for a limited period. For details, see [Microsoft Graph subscriptions - deprecating TLS 1.0 and 1.1](https://developer.microsoft.comhttps://docs.microsoft.com/graph/blogs/microsoft-graph-subscriptions-deprecating-tls-1-0-and-1-1/).
ChangeList.Target: subscription,Microsoft Graph subscriptions - deprecating TLS 1.0 and 1.1

ChangeList.Description: Added application-level and delegated Policy.ReadWrite.ApplicationConfiguration permission for read and write operations on application configuration policies.

Added [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/informationprotection-post-threatassessmentrequests?view=graph-rest-1.0), [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/threatassessmentrequest-get?view=graph-rest-1.0) and [list](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/informationprotection-list-threatassessmentrequests?view=graph-rest-1.0) APIs to manage [threatAssessmentRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/threatAssessmentRequest?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources.

Added the [user: reprocessLicenseAssignment API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-reprocesslicenseassignment), which can be used to reprocess all group-based license assignments for the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Updated the existing policies collection with a [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-beta) URL segment. Typed policy resources are now grouped under the policies segment as described in [this blog post](https://developer.microsoft.com/identity/blogs/breaking-changes-policy-api-microsoft-graph-beta/). This update adds four typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) and
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

[claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

[homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

[tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.
Added the servicePrincipal property to [List provisioningObjectSummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioning-object-summary-list?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added the **identities** property to the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource. This property represents the set of identities (like local accounts and social accounts) that this user can use to sign in with.

Added the **hideFromAddressLists** and **hideFromOutlookClients** properties to the [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity, to control the visibility of a group in the Outlook UI.

Updated the behavior of the **appRoleAssignments** and **appRoleAssignedTo** relationships on [servicePrincipal](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/serviceprincipal.md) to return the roles as documented. **appRoleAssignments** returns app roles granted to the service principal and **appRoleAssignedTo** returns principals granted app roles to the service principal.
Added the new entity type [accessPackageResourceRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/accesspackageresourcerequest?view=graph-rest-beta).

Feature rollout policy helps tenant administrators to pilot features to specific groups before enabling them for entire organization.

Introduced the new resource type [applicationTemplate](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/applicationtemplate.md). This resource type supports [instantiate](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/applicationtemplate-instantiate.md), [list](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/applicationtemplate-instantiate.md) and [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/applicationtemplate-get.md) applications from the Azure AD application gallery.

Added new resources: </br> [detailsInfo](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/detailsInfo?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [initiator](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/initiator?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [modifiedProperty](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/modifiedProperty?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [provisionedIdentity](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisionedIdentity?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [provisioningObjectsummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioningObjectsummary?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [provisioningStep](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioningStep?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [provisioningsystemDetails](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioningsystemDetails?view=graph-rest-beta)</br> [statusBase](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/statusBase?view=graph-rest-beta)
Added the [List provisioningObjectSummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioning-object-summary-list?view=graph-rest-beta) operation</br>
Added the **signInSessionsValidFromDateTime** property on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.

Added the [revokeSignInSessions](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-revokesigninsessions?view=graph-rest-1.0) action on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.
Added the **lastPasswordChangeDateTime** property to the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added **assignedlabels** property to the [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-beta) entity. This property represents the list of sensitivity label pairs (label ID, label name) associated with a group.
Added the [riskyUserHistoryItem](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/riskyuserhistoryitem?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added the [list history](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/riskyuser-list-history?view=graph-rest-beta) operation.

Added new application permissions for **access reviews** APIs: AccessReview.Read.All, ProgramControl.Read.All and ProgramControl.ReadWrite.All. For details, see the [access reviews API reference](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/accessreviews-root?view=graph-rest-beta).

Add the **signInSessionsValidFromDateTime** property on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-beta) resource. This is a rename of the **refreshTokensValidFromDateTime** properties, but both properties will be supported to allow clients to migrate smoothly. In the next couple months the old property, **refreshTokensValidFromDateTime** will be removed.

Add the **revokeSignInSessions** action on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-beta) resource. This is a rename of the **invalidateAllRefreshTokens** action, but both service actions will be supported to allow clients to migrate smoothly. In the next couple months the old service action, **invalidateAllRefreshTokens** will be removed.

Introduced a new resource type [trustFrameworkPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/trustframeworkpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) to support [Azure Active Directory B2C](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/active-directory-b2c/active-directory-b2c-overview). This resource type supports  [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/trustframework-post-trustframeworkpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta), [list](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/trustframework-list-trustframeworkpolicies?view=graph-rest-beta), [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/trustframeworkpolicy-get?view=graph-rest-beta), [update](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/trustframework-put-trustframeworkpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta), and [delete](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/trustframerkpolicy-delete?view=graph-rest-beta) operations.

ChangeList.ChangedApiName: audit logs APIs for Azure AD
ChangeList.Description: Introduced the new **audit logs APIs for Azure AD** providing activity logs for directory management tasks through [directoryAudit](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/directoryAudit?view=graph-rest-1.0) and sign-in activity through [signIns](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/signIns?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Add the **passwordNotificationWindowInDays** and **passwordValidityPeriodInDays** properties on the [domain](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/domain?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.
Add the **complianceExpirationDateTime**, **profileType** and **systemLabels** properties on the [device](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/device?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.
Add the **isResourceAccount** property on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource.

Introduced [Confirm riskyUsers compromised](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/riskyusers-confirmcompromised?view=graph-rest-beta) method, which allows admins to confirm users as compromised in Azure AD Identity Protection.

Introduced [Dismiss riskyUsers](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/riskyusers-dismiss?view=graph-rest-beta) method, which allows admins to dismiss users marked as risky in Azure AD Identity Protection.
Introduced **isProcessing** property to the [riskyUser](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/riskyuser?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.

The [targetResource](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/targetresource?view=graph-rest-beta) type now includes properties previously available to derived types that are no longer supported.

The following derived types are no longer supported and have been removed: **targetResourceDevice**, **targetResourceDirectory**, **targetResourceGroup**, **targetResourcePolicy**, **targetResourceRole**, **targetResourceServicePrincipal**, **targetResourceUser**, and **targetResourceOther**.
Add the **passwordNotificationWindowInDays** and **passwordValidityPeriodInDays** properties on the [domain](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/domain?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added new resource type [directoryObjectPartnerReference](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/directoryobjectpartnerreference?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Add the **createdDateTime** property on [organization](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/organization?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Updated the **companyName** property on the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource to be writeable.

To support configuring an identity provider in an Azure AD B2C tenant, introduced new resource type [identityProvider](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/identityprovider?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity and the [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/identityprovider-post-identityproviders?view=graph-rest-1.0), [list](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/identityprovider-list?view=graph-rest-1.0), [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/identityprovider-get?view=graph-rest-1.0), [update](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/identityprovider-update?view=graph-rest-1.0), and [delete](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/identityprovider-delete?view=graph-rest-1.0) operations.
Added the **createdDateTime** property to the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.

Added new method transitiveMembers on [groups](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/group-list-transitivemembers?view=graph-rest-1.0). This method returns a flat list of members including nested members.

Added new method transitiveMemberOf on [users](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-list-transitivemembersof?view=graph-rest-1.0), [groups](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/group-list-transitivemembersof?view=graph-rest-beta) and [devices](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/device-list-transitivemembersof?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Added new properties to [users](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0): **employeeId**, **faxNumber**, **onPremisesDistinguishedName**, **showInAddressList** and **otherMails**.
Added the **forceChangePasswordNextSignInWithMfa** property to the [passwordProfile](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/passwordprofile?view=graph-rest-1.0) complex type.

Added the **licenseAssignmentStates** property to the [User](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity for [Group Based Licensing](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/active-directory/fundamentals/active-directory-licensing-whatis-azure-portal).
Added the **licenseAssignmentState** resource for [Group Based Licensing](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/active-directory/fundamentals/active-directory-licensing-whatis-azure-portal).

Added the **assignedLicenses**, **licenseProcessingState** and **hasMembersWithLicenseErrors** properties and **membersWithLicenseErrors** relationship to [Group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity for [Group Based Licensing](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/active-directory/fundamentals/active-directory-licensing-whatis-azure-portal).

Added the [classSettings](/graph/api/resources/teamclasssettings?view=graph-rest-1.0) property to the [team](/graph/api/resources/team?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource to allow callers to get settings specific to a team of type Class.

Added the [classSettings](/graph/api/resources/teamclasssettings?view=graph-rest-beta) property to the [team](/graph/api/resources/team?view=graph-rest-beta) resource to allow callers to get settings specific to a team of type Class.

Removed [previously announced](https://developer.microsoft.com/onenote/blogs/breaking-change-education-api-updates-in-microsoft-graph-beta) deprecated properties **grade** and **feedback** from [educationSubmission](/graph/api/resources/educationsubmission?view=graph-rest-beta). Access grades and feedback only through [educationOutcome](/graph/api/educationsubmission-list-outcomes?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added new property **closeDateTime** to [educationAssignment](/graph/api/resources/educationAssignment?view=graph-rest-beta).
Changed property names **mkcd** to **projectId** and **url** to **hostWebUrl** in [educationMakeCodeResource](/graph/api/resources/educationMakeCodeResource?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added new property **grade** to [educationClass](/graph/api/resources/educationClass?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added the new [educationRubric](/graph/api/resources/educationRubric?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.

Added APIs to manage [educationRubric](/graph/api/resources/educationRubric?view=graph-rest-beta) resources on [educationUser](/graph/api/resources/educationUser?view=graph-rest-beta) and [educationAssignment](/graph/api/resources/educationAssignment?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added the new [educationOutcome](/graph/api/resources/educationOutcome?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added APIs to manage [educationOutcome](/graph/api/resources/educationOutcome?view=graph-rest-beta) resources on [educationSubmission](/graph/api/resources/educationSubmission?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added the new [educationMakeCodeResource](/graph/api/resources/educationMakeCodeResource?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added new property **grade** to [educationClass](/graph/api/resources/educationClass?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added taughtClasses to [educationUser](/graph/api/resources/educationUser?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added [educationCourse](/graph/api/resources/educationCourse?view=graph-rest-beta) to [educationClass](/graph/api/resources/educationClass?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added [delta](/graph/delta-query-overview) support to [educationUser](/graph/api/resources/educationUser?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added [delta](/graph/delta-query-overview) to [educationSchool](/graph/api/resources/educationSchool?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added [delta](/graph/delta-query-overview) to [educationClass](/graph/api/resources/educationClass?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added **faculty** option to [educationUserRole](/graph/api/resources/enums?view=graph-rest-beta#educationuserrole-values) enumeration.
Add the new [educationCategory](/graph/api/resources/educationCategory?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.

Add APIs to manage [educationCategory](/graph/api/resources/educationCategory?view=graph-rest-beta) resources on [educationClass](/graph/api/resources/educationClass?view=graph-rest-beta) and [educationAssignment](/graph/api/resources/educationAssignment?view=graph-rest-beta).
Add the new [educationFormResource](/graph/api/resources/educationFormResource?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Add the **recipients** property on the [educationAssignmentIndividualRecipient](/graph/api/resources/educationAssignmentIndividualRecipient?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Introduced new relatedContacts property on [educationUser](/graph/api/resources/educationUser?view=graph-rest-beta).
Introduced new relatedContacts property on [educationUser](/graph/api/resources/educationUser?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Places API available in v1. Added the [place](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/place?view=graph-rest-1.0), [room](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/room?view=graph-rest-1.0), [roomList](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/room?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources and their methods to provide rich details for locations in apps.
Added pagination support for the [places API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/place?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added new entity [calendarPermission](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendarpermission?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Added [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/calendarpermission-get?view=graph-rest-1.0), [update](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/calendarpermission-update?view=graph-rest-1.0) and [delete](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/calendarpermission-delete?view=graph-rest-1.0) APIs to manage [calendarPermission](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendarpermission?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources on [calendar](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendar?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Added the **isOnlineMeeting**, **onlineMeetingProvider** and **onlineMeeting** properties to the [event](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/event?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity. **isOnlineMeeting** and **onlineMeetingProvider** are optional parameters to the [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-post-events?view=graph-rest-1.0) and [update](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/event-update?view=graph-rest-1.0) methods of **event**.
Added the **defaultOnlineMeetingProviders** and **allowedOnlineMeetingProviders** properties to the [calendar](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendar?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Added the **isTallyingResponses** property to the [calendar](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendar?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Added the **isRemovable** property to the [calendar](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendar?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Added the **delegateMeetingMessageDeliveryOptions** property to the [mailboxSettings](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/mailboxSettings?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Support for [file attachments up to 150MB](outlook-large-attachments.md) for an [event](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/event?view=graph-rest-1.0) instance.
[Adding file attachments up to 150MB](outlook-large-attachments.md) to a [message](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/message?view=graph-rest-1.0) instance.

The [attachmentItem](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/attachmentitem?view=graph-rest-1.0) complex type, [createUploadSession](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/attachment-createuploadsession?view=graph-rest-1.0) action for the [attachment](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/attachment?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity, and the **attachmentType** enumeration.
Added the **calendarGroupId** property to the [calendar](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/calendar?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added the **isDraft** property to the [event](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/event?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added the ability to [update a room or roomlist](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/place-get?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added support for the [Mail.ReadBasic](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#mail-permissions) delegated permission and [Mail.ReadBasic.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#mail-permissions) application permission to [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-post-subscriptions?view=graph-rest-beta), [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-get?view=graph-rest-beta), [update](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-update?view=graph-rest-beta), and [delete](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-delete?view=graph-rest-beta) subscriptions for change notifications on message.

Added the **conversationIndex** property to [message](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/message?view=graph-rest-1.0) and its derived type [eventMessage](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/eventmessage?view=graph-rest-v1.0).

ChangeList.Description: Rolled back the type changes related to [findMeetingTimes](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-findmeetingtimes?view=graph-rest-beta) documented in [February 2019](#february-2019). The specific changes are listed in the following rows.

Changed the data type of the following parameters of [findMeetingTimes](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-findmeetingtimes?view=graph-rest-beta):
**attendees**: from **attendeeDataModel** back to [attendeeBase](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/attendeebase?view=graph-rest-beta)
**locationConstraint**: from **locationConstraints** back to [locationConstraint](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/locationconstraint?view=graph-rest-beta)
**timeConstraint**: from **findMeetingTimesTimeConstraints** back to [timeConstraint](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeconstraint?view=graph-rest-beta)

Changed the return type of **findMeetingTimes** from **findMeetingTimesResponse** back to [meetingTimeSuggestionsResult](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/meetingTimeSuggestionsResult?view=graph-rest-beta)

Changed the base type of [locationConstraintItem](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/locationconstraintitem?view=graph-rest-beta) from **locationDataModel** back to [location](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/location?view=graph-rest-beta)

Changed the data types of the following properties of [meetingTimeSuggestion](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/meetingtimesuggestion?view=graph-rest-beta):
**attendeeAvailability**: from collection of **attendeeAvailabilityDataModel** back to collection of [attendeeAvailability](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/attendeeavailability?view=graph-rest-beta)
**locations**: from collection of **locationDataModel** back to collection of [location](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/location?view=graph-rest-beta)
**meetingTimeSlot**: from **meetingTimeSlotDataModel** back to [timeSlot](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeslot?view=graph-rest-beta)
**organizerAvailability**: from **availabilityStatus** back to **freeBusyStatus**

Complex types:
**attendeeAvailabilityDataModel**
**attendeeDataModel**
**findMeetingTimesResponse**
**findMeetingTimesTimeConstraints**
**locationConstraints**
**meetingTimeSlotDataModel**
**searchWindowTimeSlot**

Enumerations:
**addressType**
**availabilityStatus**

[attendeeAvailability](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/attendeeavailability?view=graph-rest-beta)
[locationConstraint](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/locationconstraint?view=graph-rest-beta)

**meetingTimeSlot**: from [timeSlot](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeslot?view=graph-rest-beta) to [meetingTimeSlotDataModel](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/meetingtimeslotdatamodel?view=graph-rest-beta)

ChangeList.ChangedApiName: chatMessage,Set up change notifications for chat messages, including message properties (preview)
ChangeList.Description: Added support for subscribing to notifications that include resource data. Currently supported resources are [chatMessage](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/chatmessage?view=graph-rest-beta) resources in Microsoft Teams channels and chats. Subscribing apps will have to implement additional authorization and decryption code to benefit from this feature. For more details, see [Set up change notifications for chat messages, including message properties (preview)](webhooks-with-resource-data.md).
ChangeList.Target: chatMessage,Set up change notifications for chat messages, including message properties (preview)

ChangeList.Description: Added the [Create and send notifications](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-post-notifications?view=graph-rest-beta) API to enable targeting users without managing the on-behalf-of tokens.

Introduced the **targetPolicy** property on the [notification](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/projectrome-notification?view=graph-rest-beta) resource to enable web endpoints to be targeted via webpush.

Added the **fallbackPolicy** property on the [notification](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/projectrome-notification?view=graph-rest-beta) resource to enable guaranteed delivery on iOS for high-priority notifications.

Added two types of lifecycle notifications, **subscriptionRemoved** and **missed**, available for Outlook resources. Subscribing apps can take appropriate actions to mitigate notification interruptions. For more details, see [Reduce missing subscriptions and notifications for Outlook resources (preview)](webhooks-outlook-authz.md).
ChangeList.Target: Reduce missing subscriptions and notifications for Outlook resources (preview)

ChangeList.Description: Added new delegated permissions [AppCatalog.Read.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#appcatalog-resource-permissions), [ChatMessage.Send](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#chatmessage-permissions), [Teams.Create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#teams-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadForUser](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadWriteForUser](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadWriteSelfForUser](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions).

Added new application permissions [Teams.Create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#teams-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadForUser.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadWriteForUser.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions), [TeamsAppInstallation.ReadWriteSelfForUser.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#Teams-app-installation-permissions).
Added the **azureADAppId** property to [teamsAppDefinition](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/teamsAppDefinition?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added permissions for [resource-specific consent](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#teams-resource-specific-consent-permissions).
Added support for sending [channel messages](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/chatmessage?view=graph-rest-1.0) and channel message replies.
Added support for getting the **filesFolder** of a [channel](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/channel?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Introduced the Shifts APIs, including [shift](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/shift?view=graph-rest-1.0), [workforceintegration](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/workforceintegration?view=graph-rest-1.0), and associated methods.
Added new property **supportedEntities** to [workforceintegration](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/workforceintegration?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.
Added support for ChannelMessage.Read.All to APIs for reading [chatMessages](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/chatmessage?view=graph-rest-beta) in channels.
Added new entity [teamwork](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/teamwork?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added [notifications](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-post-subscriptions?view=graph-rest-beta) for all channel messages in tenant and all chat messages in tenant.
Added the [swapShiftsChangeRequest: decline](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/swapshiftschangerequest-decline?view=graph-rest-beta) method to the **swapShiftsChangeRequest** resource.
Added **primaryChannel** navigation property to team resource type.
Added [notifications](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/subscription-post-subscriptions?view=graph-rest-beta) for new and edited channel messages, and new and edited chat messages.
Added the [shiftpreferences](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/shiftpreferences?view=graph-rest-beta) resource and associated methods.
Added new relationship **shiftPreferences** to [userSettings](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/usersettings?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Updated the application permissions required to perform read and write operations for shifts resources, including [schedule](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/schedule?view=graph-rest-beta), [schedulingGroup](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/schedulinggroup?view=graph-rest-beta), [shift](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/shift?view=graph-rest-beta), [timeOff](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeoff?view=graph-rest-beta), [timeOffReason](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeoffreason?view=graph-rest-beta), [timeOffRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeoffrequest?view=graph-rest-beta), [swapShiftChangeRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/swapshiftchangerequest?view=graph-rest-beta), and [openShiftChangeRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/openshiftchangerequest?view=graph-rest-beta). **Note:** Applications permissions are currently in private preview and are not available for public use.

Added the [openshift](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/openshift?view=graph-rest-beta), [openshiftChangeRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/openshiftChangeRequest?view=graph-rest-beta), [swapShiftChangeRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/swapShiftChangeRequest?view=graph-rest-beta), and [timeoffrequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/timeoffrequest?view=graph-rest-beta) resources and associated methods.

Added the **timeClockEnabled**, **openShiftsEnabled**, **swapShiftsRequestsEnabled**, **offerShiftRequestsEnabled**,  **timeOffRequestsEnabled** properties to the [schedule](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/schedule?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added an additional route to retrieve a [driveItem] using a team and channel ID, [get driveItem](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/driveitem-get?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added the [Get team photo](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/team-get-photo?view=graph-rest-beta) and [Update team photo](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/team-update-photo?view=graph-rest-beta) methods.
[Reading images in messages](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/chatmessagehostedcontent-get?view=graph-rest-beta) now support application permissions.
Added the **primaryChannel** property to the [team](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/team?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added the **allowCreatePrivateChannels** property to the [teamMemberSettings](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/teammembersettings?view=graph-rest-beta) resource.
Added the ability to pull incremental messages from channels with the [channel messages delta query API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/channel-messages-delta?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added new reports for retrieving user registration and usage information:,
  • [reportroot-getcredentialusagesummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-getcredentialusagesummary?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset.
  • [reportroot-getcredentialuserregistrationcount](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-getcredentialuserregistrationcount?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports the number of registrations for self-service password reset and multi-factor authentication.
  • [reportroot-list-credentialuserregistrationdetails](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/reportroot-list-credentialuserregistrationdetails?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset and multi-factor authentication.
  • [reportroot-list-usercredentialusagedetails](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/reportroot-list-usercredentialusagedetails?view=graph-rest-beta) - Reports usage of self-service password reset for a user.

Added **ownerPrincipalName** property to the [sharePointSiteUsageDetail](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/sharePointSiteUsageDetail?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added the **office365Active** and **office365Inactive** properties to the [office365ServicesUserCounts](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/office365ServicesUserCounts?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Insights API is available in v1.0. This includes the [officeGraphInsights](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/officegraphinsights?view=graph-rest-1.0), [trending](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-trending?view=graph-rest-1.0), [usedInsight](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-used?view=graph-rest-1.0), and [sharedInsight](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/insights-shared?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources, and related types and methods. See [Why integrate with document-based insights?](social-intel-concept-overview.md#why-integrate-with-document-based-insights) for more information.
Added the [profile API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/profile?view=graph-rest-beta) and associated methods.

Introduced the new workplace intelligence [analytics API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/useranalytics?view=graph-rest-beta) that enables you to get analytics about how users spend their time on various activities during and outside of working hours, including calls, chats (instant messages), emails, focus work, and meetings.

Introduced the new workplace intelligence [settings API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/settings?view=graph-rest-beta) that represents the current required settings for a user to use the [analytics API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/useranalytics?view=graph-rest-beta).

Introduced the new [activityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type and the following new resource types that are derived from it: [callActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/callactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), [chatActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/chatactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta),[emailActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/emailactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), [focusActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/focusactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta), and [meetingActivityStatistics](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/meetingactivitystatistics?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added support for [subscription](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/subscription) to the **user** resource in [Microsoft Cloud China operated by 21Vianet](deployments.md).

Added [unifiedRoleAssignmentMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/unifiedroleassignmentmultiple?view=graph-rest-beta), [rbacApplicationMultiple](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/rbacapplicationmultiple?view=graph-rest-beta), and [appScope](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/appscope?view=graph-rest-beta) and the following actions:

    • .
Added support for [delta queries for administrativeUnits](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/administrativeunit-delta?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added support for [delta queries for oAuth2PermissionGrant](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/oauth2permissiongrant-delta?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added the [authenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/authenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta), [passwordAuthenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/passwordauthenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta), and [phoneAuthenticationMethod](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/phoneauthenticationmethod?view=graph-rest-beta) resources and associated methods.
Added the **createdByAppId** property to the [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Typed policy resources are grouped under the [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-1.0) URL segment. This update adds five typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) and
  • [tokenIssuancePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

Added the [claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

Added the [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

Added the [tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.

Added the [tokenIssuancePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource type, which controls the characteristics of SAML tokens issued by Azure AD. This allows you to set the signing algorithm, signing options, or SAML token version to be used to issue the SAML token.

Added the PrivilegedAccess.Read.AzureResources application permission for [Privileged Identity Management - Azure resources](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/privilegedidentitymanagement-resources?view=graph-rest-beta).
Added the [Auditlogs.Read.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#user-permissions) permission for listing the sign-in activity of a user.

Added the [identitySecurityDefaultsEnforcementPolicy API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/identitysecuritydefaultsenforcementpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta), which represents Azure Active Directory security defaults policy.
Added support for the **$top** and **$skiptoken** filters to support pagination on the [List provisioningObjectSummary](/api-reference/beta/api/provisioningobjectsummary-list) method.
Added the **authenticationRequirement** property and the **riskEventTypes_v2** property to the [signin](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/signin?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity.
Added support for [delta queries for orgContact](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/orgcontact-delta?view=graph-rest-1.0).
Added new user permission [User.ManageIdentities.All](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/permissions-reference#user-permissions).
Updated the conditional access APIs to use the /identity/ segment; for example, /beta/identity/conditionalAccess/policies.
Added the **devices** property to the [conditionalaccessconditionset](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/conditionalaccessconditionset?view=graph-rest-beta) entity.

Added the [group: assignLicense API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/group-assignlicense?view=graph-rest-1.0), which can be used to assign license to a [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Updated the existing policies collection with a [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-beta) URL segment. Typed policy resources are now grouped under the policies segment as described in [this blog post](https://developer.microsoft.com/identity/blogs/breaking-changes-policy-api-microsoft-graph-beta/). This update adds four typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) and
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

Added the [claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

Added the [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

Added the [tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.

Added the [tokenIssuancePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenissuancepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type, which controls the characteristics of SAML tokens issued by Azure AD. This allows you to set the signing algorithm, signing options, or SAML token version to be used to issue the SAML token.
Added the [error](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/synchronization-synchronizationError?view=graph-rest-beta) property to the **quarantineStatus** resource type.

Updated the [accessPackageAssignmentPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/accesspackageassignmentpolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) with additional properties for requestor, approval and review settings.

Added the **latestSupportedTlsVersion** property to the [subscription](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/subscription?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity. Specifies the latest TLS version that the notification endpoint supports. Allows subscribers to use a deprecated version of TLS for a limited period. For details, see [Microsoft Graph subscriptions - deprecating TLS 1.0 and 1.1](https://developer.microsoft.comhttps://docs.microsoft.com/graph/blogs/microsoft-graph-subscriptions-deprecating-tls-1-0-and-1-1/).
ChangeList.Target: subscription,Microsoft Graph subscriptions - deprecating TLS 1.0 and 1.1

ChangeList.Description: Added application-level and delegated Policy.ReadWrite.ApplicationConfiguration permission for read and write operations on application configuration policies.

Added [create](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/informationprotection-post-threatassessmentrequests?view=graph-rest-1.0), [get](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/threatassessmentrequest-get?view=graph-rest-1.0) and [list](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/informationprotection-list-threatassessmentrequests?view=graph-rest-1.0) APIs to manage [threatAssessmentRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/threatAssessmentRequest?view=graph-rest-1.0) resources.

Added the [user: reprocessLicenseAssignment API](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/user-reprocesslicenseassignment), which can be used to reprocess all group-based license assignments for the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0).

Updated the existing policies collection with a [policies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/policy-overview?view=graph-rest-beta) URL segment. Typed policy resources are now grouped under the policies segment as described in [this blog post](https://developer.microsoft.com/identity/blogs/breaking-changes-policy-api-microsoft-graph-beta/). This update adds four typed policy resources:
  • [activityBasedTimeoutPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [claimsMappingPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)
  • [homeRealmDiscoveryPolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) and
  • [tokenLifetimePolicies](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta)

Added [activityBasedTimeoutPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/activityBasedTimeoutPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls automatic sign-out for web sessions after a period of inactivity, for applications that support activity-based timeout functionality.

[claimsMappingPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/claimsMappingPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls the claims mapping for WS-Fed, SAML, OAuth 2.0, and OpenID Connect protocols, for tokens issued to a specific application.

[homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/homeRealmDiscoveryPolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls Azure Active Directory authentication behavior for federated users, in particular for auto-acceleration and user authentication restrictions in federated domains.

[tokenLifetimePolicy](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/tokenlifetimepolicy?view=graph-rest-beta) resource type controls the lifetime duration of access tokens used to access protected resources.
Added the servicePrincipal property to [List provisioningObjectSummary](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/provisioning-object-summary-list?view=graph-rest-beta).

Added the **identities** property to the [user](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/user?view=graph-rest-1.0) resource. This property represents the set of identities (like local accounts and social accounts) that this user can use to sign in with.

Added the **hideFromAddressLists** and **hideFromOutlookClients** properties to the [group](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/group?view=graph-rest-1.0) entity, to control the visibility of a group in the Outlook UI.

Updated the behavior of the **appRoleAssignments** and **appRoleAssignedTo** relationships on [servicePrincipal](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/serviceprincipal.md) to return the roles as documented. **appRoleAssignments** returns app roles granted to the service principal and **appRoleAssignedTo** returns principals granted app roles to the service principal.
Added the new entity type [accessPackageResourceRequest](https://docs.microsoft.com/graph/api/resources/accesspackageresourcerequest?view=graph-rest-beta).
